16. Add or replace only movable furniture and decor. Never alter architecture.
17. If you cannot place a catalogue product without changing the room architecture, omit that product rather than altering the room.
18. Keep the output photorealistic and consistent with the user's requested style.
19. Keep the room type correct.
20. Use shortlist objects with strong visual alignment to the references.
21. If the user asks for color/material/style changes, apply those to shortlist-aligned products rather than switching to unrelated products.
${editText}
${targetedEditText}
${retryText}
Return one final redesigned room image only.
